00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:20,090
A vox gon out of þe wode go,

7
00:00:20,090 --> 00:00:22,830
Afingret so, þat him wes wo;

8
00:00:22,830 --> 00:00:25,220
He nes nevere in none wise

9
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:28,380
Afingret erour half so swiþe.

10
00:00:28,380 --> 00:00:31,370
He ne hoeld nouþer wey ne strete,

11
00:00:31,370 --> 00:00:34,150
For him wes loþ men to mete;

12
00:00:34,150 --> 00:00:37,230
Him were levere meten one hen,

13
00:00:37,230 --> 00:00:40,050
Þen half an oundred wimmen.

14
00:00:40,050 --> 00:00:42,930
He strok swiþe over-al,

15
00:00:42,930 --> 00:00:45,750
So þat he ofsei ane wal;

16
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:48,380
Wiþinne þe walle wes on hous,

17
00:00:48,380 --> 00:00:51,100
Þe wox wes þider swiþe wous;

18
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:53,850
For he þouhte his hounger aquenche,

19
00:00:53,850 --> 00:00:56,530
Oþer mid mete, oþer mid drenche.

20
00:00:56,530 --> 00:01:00,250
Abouten he biheld wel ȝerne;

21
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:03,670
Þo eroust bigon þe vox to erne.

22
00:01:03,670 --> 00:01:06,770
Al fort he come to one walle,

23
00:01:06,770 --> 00:01:09,680
And som þer-of wes afalle,

24
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:12,870
And wes þe wal over-al to-broke,

25
00:01:12,870 --> 00:01:15,700
And on ȝat þer wes I-loke;

26
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:20,190
At þe furmeste bruche þat he fond,

27
00:01:20,190 --> 00:01:23,420
He lep in, and over he wond.

28
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:26,440
Þo he wes inne, smere he lou,

29
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:29,570
And þer-of he hadde gome I-nou;

30
00:01:29,570 --> 00:01:32,280
For he com in wiþ-outen leve

31
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:35,380
Boþen of haiward and of reve.

32
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:39,190
On hous þer wes, þe dore wes ope,

33
00:01:39,190 --> 00:01:42,000
Hennen weren þerinne I-crope,

34
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,840
Five, þat makeþ anne flok,

35
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:47,180
And mid hem sat on kok.

36
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:49,810
Þe kok him wes flowen on hey,

37
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:52,710
And two hennen him seten ney.

38
00:01:52,710 --> 00:01:56,540
"Wox," quod þe kok, "wat dest þou þare?

39
00:01:56,540 --> 00:01:59,770
Go hom, Crist þe ȝeve kare!

40
00:01:59,770 --> 00:02:02,780
Houre hennen þou dest ofte shome."

41
00:02:02,780 --> 00:02:06,300
"Be stille, ich hote, a godes nome!"

42
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:09,340
Quaþ þe wox, "Sire Chauntecler,

43
00:02:09,340 --> 00:02:12,520
Þou fle adoun, and com me ner.

44
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:15,340
I nabbe don her nout bote goed,

45
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:18,810
I have leten þine hennen blod;

46
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:21,660
Hy weren seke ounder þe ribe,

47
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:24,880
Þat hy ne miȝtte non lengour libe.

48
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:28,120
Bote here heddre were I-take;

49
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:31,730
Þat I do for almes sake.

50
00:02:31,730 --> 00:02:35,150
Ich have hem letten eddre blod,

51
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:38,970
And þe, Chauntecler, hit wolde don goed.

52
00:02:38,970 --> 00:02:42,690
Þou havest þat ilke ounder þe splen,

53
00:02:42,690 --> 00:02:46,020
Þou nestes nevere daies ten;

54
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:49,080
For þine lif-dayes beþ al ago,

55
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:51,310
Bote þou bi mine rede do;

56
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:55,520
I do þe lete blod ounder þe brest,

57
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:58,990
Oþer sone axe after þe prest."

58
00:02:58,990 --> 00:03:03,430
"Go wei," quod þe kok, "wo þe bi-go!

59
00:03:03,430 --> 00:03:05,570
Þou havest don oure kunne wo.

60
00:03:05,570 --> 00:03:08,130
Go mid þan þat þou havest nouþe;

61
00:03:08,130 --> 00:03:11,280
Acoursed be þou of Godes mouþe!

62
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:15,280
For were I adoun bi Godes nome!

63
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:19,800
Ich miȝte ben siker of oþre shome.

64
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:22,370
Ac weste hit houre cellerer,

65
00:03:22,370 --> 00:03:24,830
Þat þou were I-comen her.

66
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:28,850
He wolde sone after þe ȝonge,

67
00:03:28,850 --> 00:03:32,240
Mid pikes and stones and staves stronge;

68
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:35,730
Alle þine bones he wolde to-breke;

69
00:03:35,730 --> 00:03:38,520
Þene we weren wel awreke."

70
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:41,860
He wes stille, ne spak namore,

71
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:45,270
Ac he werþ aþurst wel sore;

72
00:03:45,270 --> 00:03:48,330
Þe þurst him dede more wo,

73
00:03:48,330 --> 00:03:50,650
Þen hevede raþer his hounger do.

74
00:03:50,650 --> 00:03:54,010
Over-al he ede and souhte;

75
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:57,030
On aventure his witt him brouhte,

76
00:03:57,030 --> 00:04:00,160
To one putte wes water inne

77
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:03,330
Þat wes I-maked mid grete ginne.

78
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:05,600
Tuo boketes þer he founde,

79
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:08,100
Þat oþer wende to þe grounde,

80
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:11,400
Þat wen me shulde þat on opwinde,

81
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:14,640
Þat oþer wolde adoun winde.

82
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:17,330
He ne hounderstod nout of þe ginne,

83
00:04:17,330 --> 00:04:21,370
He nom þat boket, and lep þerinne;

84
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:24,200
For he hopede I-nou to drinke.

85
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:27,340
Þis boket biginneþ to sinke;

86
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:30,370
To late þe vox wes biþout,

87
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:33,080
Þo he wes in þe ginne I-brout.

88
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:36,030
I-nou he gon him bi-þenche,

89
00:04:36,030 --> 00:04:38,310
Ac hit ne halp mid none wrenche;

90
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:41,810
Adoun he moste, he wes þerinne;-

91
00:04:41,810 --> 00:04:45,290
I-kaut he wes mid swikele ginne.

92
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:48,900
Hit miȝte han iben wel his wille

93
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:51,870
To lete þat boket hongi stille.

94
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:54,650
Wat mid serewe and mid drede,

95
00:04:54,650 --> 00:04:57,410
Al his þurst him over-hede.

96
00:04:57,410 --> 00:05:00,090
Al þus he com to þe grounde,

97
00:05:00,090 --> 00:05:03,270
And water I-nou þer he founde.

98
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:06,550
Þo he fond water, ȝerne he dronk,

99
00:05:06,550 --> 00:05:09,790
Him þoute þat water þere stonk,

100
00:05:09,790 --> 00:05:12,660
For hit wes to-ȝeines his wille.

101
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:16,920
"Wo worþe," quaþ þe vox, "lust and wille,

102
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:19,500
Þat ne can meþ to his mete!

103
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:22,670
Ȝef ich nevede to muchel I-ete,

104
00:05:22,670 --> 00:05:25,590
Þis ilke shome neddi nouþe;

105
00:05:25,590 --> 00:05:28,380
Nedde lust I-ben of mine mouþe.

106
00:05:28,380 --> 00:05:31,200
Him is wo in euche londe,

107
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,690
Þat is þef mid his honde.

108
00:05:33,690 --> 00:05:37,070
Ich am I-kaut mid swikele ginne,

109
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:39,970
Oþer soum devel me broute her-inne.

110
00:05:39,970 --> 00:05:43,070
I was woned to ben wiis,

111
00:05:43,070 --> 00:05:46,260
Ac nou of me I-don hit hiis."

112
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:49,550
Þe vox wep, and reuliche bigan.

113
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:52,980
Þer com a wolf gon after þan

114
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:55,430
Out of þe depe wode blive,

115
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:57,910
For he wes afingret swiþe.

116
00:05:57,910 --> 00:06:01,100
Noþing he ne founde in al þe niȝte,

117
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:04,320
Wer-mide his honger aquenche miȝtte.

118
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:08,130
He com to þe putte, þene vox I-herde;

119
00:06:08,130 --> 00:06:11,150
He him kneu wel bi his rerde,

120
00:06:11,150 --> 00:06:13,490
For hit wes his neiȝebore,

121
00:06:13,490 --> 00:06:16,510
And his gossip, of children bore.

122
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:19,290
A-doun bi þe putte he sat.

123
00:06:19,290 --> 00:06:22,650
Quod þe wolf, "Wat may ben þat

124
00:06:22,650 --> 00:06:25,310
Þat ich in þe putte I-here?

125
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:28,630
Hertou Cristine, oþer mi fere?

126
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:32,040
Say me soþ, ne gabbe þou me nout,

127
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:35,080
Wo haveþ þe in þe putte, I-brout?"

128
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:38,680
Þe vox hine I-kneu wel for his kun,

129
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:41,480
And þo eroust kom wiit to him;

130
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:44,210
For he þoute mid soumme ginne,

131
00:06:44,210 --> 00:06:48,470
Him-self houpbringe, þene wolf þerinne.

132
00:06:48,470 --> 00:06:51,580
Quod þe vox, "Wo is nou þere?

133
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:55,060
Ich wene hit is Sigrim þat ich here."

134
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:57,890
"Þat is soþ," þe wolf sede,

135
00:06:57,890 --> 00:07:00,530
"Ac wat art þou, so God þe rede?"

136
00:07:00,530 --> 00:07:04,940
"A," quod þe vox, "ich wille þe telle;

137
00:07:04,940 --> 00:07:07,880
On alpi word ich lie nelle.

138
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:10,500
Ich am Reneuard, þi frend,

139
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,560
And ȝif ich þine come hevede I-wend,

140
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,390
Ich hedde so I-bede for þe,

141
00:07:16,390 --> 00:07:19,150
Þat þou sholdest comen to me."

142
00:07:19,150 --> 00:07:20,130
"Mid þe?"

143
00:07:20,130 --> 00:07:22,090
quod þe wolf, "War to?

144
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:24,980
Wat shulde ich ine þe putte do?"

145
00:07:24,980 --> 00:07:28,110
Quod þe vox, "Þou art ounwiis,

146
00:07:28,110 --> 00:07:31,170
Her is þe blisse of paradiis;

147
00:07:31,170 --> 00:07:34,130
Her ich mai evere wel fare,

148
00:07:34,130 --> 00:07:37,090
Wiþ-outen pine, wiþouten kare;

149
00:07:37,090 --> 00:07:40,200
Her is mete, her is drinke,

150
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:43,060
Her is blisse wiþouten swinke;

151
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:45,630
Her nis hounger nevermo,

152
00:07:45,630 --> 00:07:48,350
Ne non oþer kunnes wo;

153
00:07:48,350 --> 00:07:51,060
Of alle gode her is I-nou."

154
00:07:51,060 --> 00:07:54,490
Mid þilke wordes þe volf lou.

155
00:07:54,490 --> 00:07:57,800
"Art þou ded, so God þe rede,

156
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,620
Oþer of þe worlde?"

157
00:07:59,620 --> 00:08:01,200
þe wolf sede.

158
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:04,290
Quod þe wolf, "Wenne storve þou,

159
00:08:04,290 --> 00:08:07,180
And wat dest þou þere nou?

160
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:10,650
Ne beþ nout ȝet þre daies ago,

161
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:13,110
Þat þou and þi wif also,

162
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:16,930
And þine children, smale and grete,

163
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:20,070
Alle to-gedere mid me hete."

164
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:22,540
"Þat is soþ," quod þe vox,

165
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:24,920
"Gode þonk, nou hit is þus,

166
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:28,130
Þat ihc am to Criste vend.

167
00:08:28,130 --> 00:08:30,870
Not hit non of mine frend.

168
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:34,020
I nolde, for al þe worldes goed,

169
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:37,270
Ben ine þe worlde, þer ich hem fond.

170
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:40,280
Wat shuldich ine þe worlde go,

171
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:43,110
Þer nis bote kare and wo,

172
00:08:43,110 --> 00:08:46,060
And livie in fulþe and in sunne?

173
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:49,080
Ac her beþ joies fele cunne;

174
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,970
Her beþ boþe shep and get."

175
00:08:51,970 --> 00:08:55,280
Þe wolf haveþ hounger swiþe gret,

176
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:57,810
For he nedde ȝare I-ete;

177
00:08:57,810 --> 00:09:00,850
And þo he herde speken of mete,

178
00:09:00,850 --> 00:09:03,010
He wolde bleþeliche ben þare.

179
00:09:03,010 --> 00:09:03,560
"A!"

180
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:07,310
quod þe wolf, "gode I-fere,

181
00:09:07,310 --> 00:09:09,740
Moni goed mel þou havest me binome;

182
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:12,120
Let me adoun to þe kome.

183
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:14,420
And al ich wole þe for-ȝeve."

184
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:17,610
"Ȝe," quod þe vox, "were þou I-sriue,

185
00:09:17,610 --> 00:09:21,110
And sunnen hevedest al forsake,

186
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:23,900
And to klene lif I-take,

187
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:26,560
Ich wolde so bidde for þe,

188
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:29,240
Þat þou sholdest comen to me."

189
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:32,490
"To wom shuld ich," þe wolfe seīde,

190
00:09:32,490 --> 00:09:35,880
Ben I-knowe of mine misdede?

191
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,650
Her nis noþing alive,

192
00:09:37,650 --> 00:09:40,260
Þat me kouþe her nou srive.

193
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:42,950
Þou havest ben ofte min I-fere,

194
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:45,680
Woltou nou mi srift I-here,

195
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:48,960
And al mi liif I shal þe telle?"

196
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,620
"Nay," quod þe vox, "I nelle."

197
00:09:51,620 --> 00:09:54,680
"Neltou," quod þe wolf, "þin ore,

198
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:57,510
Ich am afingret swiþe sore;

199
00:09:57,510 --> 00:10:00,730
Ich wot to-niȝt ich worþe ded,

200
00:10:00,730 --> 00:10:03,610
Bote þou do me somne reed.

201
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:06,720
For Cristes love, be mi prest."

202
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:09,730
Þe wolf bey adoun his brest,

203
00:10:09,730 --> 00:10:12,430
And gon to siken harde and stronge.

204
00:10:12,430 --> 00:10:16,860
"Woltou," quod þe vox, "srift ounderfonge,

205
00:10:16,860 --> 00:10:19,410
Tel þine sunnen on and on,

206
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,430
Þat þer bileve never on."

207
00:10:21,430 --> 00:10:25,490
"Sone," quod þe wolf, "wel I-faie,

208
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:28,590
Ich habbe ben qued al mi lifdaie;

209
00:10:28,590 --> 00:10:31,710
Ich habbe widewene kors,

210
00:10:31,710 --> 00:10:34,390
Þerfore ich fare þe wors.

211
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:37,450
A þousent shep ich habbe abiten,

212
00:10:37,450 --> 00:10:40,180
And mo, ȝef hy weren I-writen.

213
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:43,030
Ac hit me of-þinkeþ sore.

214
00:10:43,030 --> 00:10:45,660
Maister, shal I tellen more?"

215
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:48,880
"Ȝe," quod þe vox, "al þou most sugge,

216
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:51,780
Oþer elles-wer þou most abugge."

217
00:10:51,780 --> 00:10:55,080
"Gossip," quod þe wolf, "forȝef hit me,

218
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:59,130
Ich habbe ofte sehid qued bi þe,

219
00:10:59,130 --> 00:11:01,250
Men seide þat þou on þine live

220
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:03,880
Misferdest mid mine wive;

221
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:07,270
Ich þe aperseivede one stounde,

222
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:09,990
And in bedde togedere ou founde.

223
00:11:09,990 --> 00:11:13,100
Ich wes ofte ou ful ney,

224
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:16,220
And in bedde to-gedere ou sey.

225
00:11:16,220 --> 00:11:19,560
Ich wende, al-so oþre doþ,

226
00:11:19,560 --> 00:11:22,240
Þat ich I-seie were soþ,

227
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:25,140
And þerfore þou were me loþ;

228
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:28,850
Gode gossip, ne be þou nohut wroþ."

229
00:11:28,850 --> 00:11:31,390
"Vuolf," quod þe vox him þo,

230
00:11:31,390 --> 00:11:34,720
"Al þat þou havest her bifore I-do,

231
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:38,340
In þouht, in speche, and in dede,

232
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:41,500
In euche oþeres kunnes quede,

233
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:44,090
Ich þe forȝeve at þisse nede."

234
00:11:44,090 --> 00:11:45,930
"Crist þe forȝelde!"

235
00:11:45,930 --> 00:11:47,550
þe wolf seide.

236
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:50,230
"Nou ich am in clene live,

237
00:11:50,230 --> 00:11:53,640
Ne recche ich of childe ne of wive.

238
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:56,520
Ac sei me wat I shal do,

239
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,820
And ou ich may comen þe to."

240
00:11:58,820 --> 00:11:59,710
"Do?"

241
00:11:59,710 --> 00:12:01,470
quod þe vox.

242
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:03,120
"Ich wille þe lere.

243
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:06,490
I-siist þou a boket hongi þere?

244
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:09,870
Þere is a bruche of hevene blisse,

245
00:12:09,870 --> 00:12:12,050
Lep þerinne, mid I-wisse,

246
00:12:12,050 --> 00:12:15,160
And þou shalt comen to me sone."

247
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:18,000
Quod the wolf, "þat is liȝt to done."

248
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,800
He lep in, and way sumdel;

249
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:23,610
Þat weste þe vox ful wel.

250
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:26,520
Þe wolf gon sinke, þe vox arise;

251
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:30,140
Þo gon þe wolf sore agrise.

252
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:32,600
Þo he com amidde þe putte,

253
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:35,740
Þe wolfe þene vox opward mette.

254
00:12:35,740 --> 00:12:39,070
"Gossip," quod þe wolf, "Wat nou?

255
00:12:39,070 --> 00:12:40,790
Wat hauest þou I-munt?

256
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:42,230
weder wolt þou?"

257
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:43,790
"Weder, Ich wille?"

258
00:12:43,790 --> 00:12:44,970
þe vox sede.

259
00:12:44,970 --> 00:12:47,530
"Ich wille oup, so God me rede!

260
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:50,430
And nou go doun, wiþ þi meel,

261
00:12:50,430 --> 00:12:52,910
Þi biȝete worþ wel smal.

262
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:55,270
Ac ich am þerof glad and bliþe,

263
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:58,200
Þat þou art nomen in clene live.

264
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:02,120
Þi soule-cnul ich wille do ringe,

265
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:06,340
And masse for þine soule singe."

266
00:13:06,340 --> 00:13:08,770
Þe wrecche bineþe noþing ne vind,

267
00:13:08,770 --> 00:13:12,430
Bote cold water, and hounger him bind;

268
00:13:12,430 --> 00:13:15,480
To colde gistninge he wes I-bede,

269
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:18,350
Vroggen haveþ his dou I-knede.

270
00:13:18,350 --> 00:13:20,780
Þe wolf in þe putte stod,

271
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:23,310
Afingret so þat he ves wod.

272
00:13:23,310 --> 00:13:26,500
I-nou he cursede þat þider him broute;

273
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:29,330
Þe vox þer of luitel route.

274
00:13:29,330 --> 00:13:32,220
Þe put him wes þe house ney,

275
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:35,140
Þer freren woneden swiþe sley.

276
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:37,940
Þo þat hit com to þe time,

277
00:13:37,940 --> 00:13:40,680
Þat hoe shulden arisen Ine,

278
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:43,590
For to suggen here houssong,

279
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:46,210
O frere þere wes among,

280
00:13:46,210 --> 00:13:49,160
Of here slep hem shulde awecche,

281
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:52,130
Wen hoe shulden þidere recche.

282
00:13:52,130 --> 00:13:55,420
He seide, "Ariseþ on and on,

283
00:13:55,420 --> 00:13:58,890
And komeþ to houssong hevereuch on."

284
00:13:58,890 --> 00:14:01,970
Þis ilke frere heyte ailmer;

285
00:14:01,970 --> 00:14:04,040
He wes hoere maister curtiler.

286
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:08,130
He wes hofþurst swiþe stronge;

287
00:14:08,130 --> 00:14:11,060
Riȝt amidward here houssonge

288
00:14:11,060 --> 00:14:13,900
Al-hone to þe putte he hede;

289
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,670
For he wende bete his nede.

290
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:19,180
He com to þe putte, and drou,

291
00:14:19,180 --> 00:14:22,180
And þe wolf wes hevi I-nou.

292
00:14:22,180 --> 00:14:25,250
Þe frere mid al his maine tey

293
00:14:25,250 --> 00:14:28,440
So longe þat he þene wolf I-sey!

294
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:31,560
For he sei þene wolf þer sitte,

295
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:35,550
He gradde, "Þe devel is in þe putte!"

296
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:37,630
To þe putte hy gounnen gon,

297
00:14:37,630 --> 00:14:40,880
Alle mid pikes and staves and ston,

298
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,450
Euch mon mid þat he hedde;

299
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:46,570
Wo wes him þat wepne nedde.

300
00:14:46,570 --> 00:14:49,640
Hy comen to þe putte þene wolf opdrowe;

301
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:52,960
Þo hede þe wreche fomen I-nowe,

302
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:55,970
Þat weren egre him to slete

303
00:14:55,970 --> 00:14:58,830
Mid grete houndes, and to bete.

304
00:14:58,830 --> 00:15:01,920
Wel and wroþe he wes I-swonge,

305
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:05,540
Mid staves and speres he wes I-stounge.

306
00:15:05,540 --> 00:15:08,110
Þe wox bicharde him, mid I-wisse,

307
00:15:08,110 --> 00:15:11,570
For he ne fond nones kunnes blisse,

308
00:15:11,570 --> 00:15:15,100
Ne hof duntes forȝevenesse.

309
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:23,130
End of
Þe Vox and þe Wolf
